            <div id="planning">
                <h2>Planning</h2>
                <p><b>Prep Time:</b> X minutes</p>
                <p><b>Cook Time:</b> 13-14 minutes</p>
                <p><b>Servings:</b> 8-12 bites <p>
            </div> 

            <div id="preparation">
                <h2>Preparation</h2>
                <h3>Equipment</h3>
                <ul>
                    <li>Baking pan</li>
                    <li>Oven</li>

                    
                </ul>
                <h3>Ingredients</h3>
                <ul>
                    <li>Rolled oats, 1 cup</li>
                    <li>Oat flour, 1 cup</li>
                    <li>Baking Powder, 1 tsp</li>
                    <li>Cinnamon, 1/2 tsp</li>
                    <li>Sea salt, 1/4 tsp</li>
                    <li>Grated Nutmeg, 1/8-1/4 tsp</li>
                    <li>PUreed overripe banana, 1 cup (~2 large bananas)</li>
                    <li>Vanilla extract, 1 1/2 tsp</li>
                    <li>Non-dairy chocolate chips, 3 Tbsp</li>
                    <li>OPTIONAL: add chia or flax</li>
                    
                </ul>
            </div>

            <div id="cooking">
                <h2>Cooking</h2>
                <ol>
                    <li>Preheat oven to 350deg</li>
                    <li>In large bowl combine oats, oat flour, baking powder, cinnamon, sea salt, and nutmeg</li>
                    <li>Add the pureed bananas, vanilla extract, and chocolate chips to the driy mixture, stir until combined</li>
                    <li>Place 2-Tbsp scoops of batter on a lined cookie sheet</li>
                    <li>Bake for 13-14 minutes, or until just firm to the touch</li>
                                        
                </ol>

            </div>

            <div id="notes">
                <h2>Notes & Tips</h2>
                <ul>
                    <li>Yum</li>
                    
